# Action Tracker and Context Rule

Whenever you start a new conversation or session, your VERY FIRST action should be to read the `docs/action_tracker.md` file — especially the **"Session Handoff"** section at the top if present (current pickup point for in-progress work).

For the full doc map (which file to read or update), see `docs/DOCUMENTATION.md`.

**Read only the top:** Session Handoff + Open items (~50 lines). Do not read the full file unless investigating history.

**When editing this file:** follow `docs/doc_hygiene.md` — one Session Handoff, no Phase 0–6 specs, no doc index tables, no long DONE narratives. Archive old handoffs to `docs/archive/`.

This file tracks current pickup and prioritized backlog only. Historical detail: `docs/archive/implementation_log_2026-05.md`.